HEADWORD: Planimeter
<hw>Pla*nim"e*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Plani-</ets> + <ets>-meter</ets>. Cf.
<er>Planometer</er>.]</ety> <def>An instrument for measuring the area of
any plane figure, however irregular, by passing a tracer around the
bounding line; a platometer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

